1.12	Changi_Airport_Skytrain	Changi Airport Skytrain	The Changi Airport Skytrain is a people mover system that connects Terminals 1, 2 and 3 at Singapore Changi Airport. Opened in 1990, it was the first auto-guided system in Asia. The Changi Airport Skytrain operates from 0500 to 0230 daily and operates at 1 to 2 minute intervals. Travel on the Skytrain is free and an inter-terminal journey takes about 90 seconds. All stations have platform screen doors, are air conditioned and have plasma displays indicating the arrival time of the next train.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/CrystalMover-Changi-Ext.JPG/300px-CrystalMover-Changi-Ext.JPG
